Previously the federated covariance test only considered the case of regular covariance. The test has now been modified to account for the weighted covariance and, in particular, 3 following cases:
1. One input matrix is federated, another input matrix and weights matrix are not;
2. Both input matrices are federated, weights are not;
3. Both input and weights matrices are federated.
